1 lb ground lamb
1 egg, lightly beaten
3 cloves garlic, minced
2 tbsp parsley
2 tsp oregano
1 tsp cumin
salt
pepper
1/4 tsp crushed red pepper flakes
oil

Sauce:
1.5 cup yogurt
1/2 cup mayonnaise
1.5 c basil leaves
1/2 cup parsley leaves
1/4 cup chopped chives
1/4 cup oregano
Juice of 1 lemon
2 cloves garlic
salt
pepper

Preheat oven to 425 deg. F. Line baking sheet. In large bowl, combine lamb, egg, garlic, parsley, oregano, cumin, salt, pepper, red pepper flakes. Form into balls and place on baking sheet.Â 
Drizzle meatballs with oil and bake until golden; about 20 minutes.

Sauce: Blend together ingredients. Season and taste.
